Package org.jgrapes.io.events

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Accepted<T extends java.nio.Buffer>
    This event signals that a new connection has been made by a client.
    Close<C extends Connection>  
    Closed<C extends Connection>
    This event signals that an I/O connection has been closed.
    ConnectionEvent<T,C extends Connection>
    Base class for events related to a DataConnection.
    Eof
    This event signals the end of data from a stream.
    FileOpened<T extends java.nio.Buffer>  
    IOError
    A special kind of Error that signals problems during IO.
    NioRegistration  
    NioRegistration.Completed  
    NioRegistration.Registration  
    Opened<C extends Connection>
    This event signals that an I/O resource has successfully been opened (usually in response to some ...Open event).
    OpenFile
    Signals a File component that it should start working with a new file.
    Read<T extends java.nio.Buffer>
    This event signals that a new chunk of data has successfully been obtained from some source.
    Ready
    Signals that a server has bound to a socket address and is ready to accept connections.
    Write<T extends java.nio.Buffer>
    This event signals that a new chunk of data is to be forwarded to the destination.
